<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,835,1077]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Only three species have been described from 
<collectingCountry box="[665,774,835,861]" name="Indonesia" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
of this moderately large cosmopolitan genus of 64 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Gagne, R. J. &amp; Jaschhof, M." box="[159,431,871,897]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref58587" refString="Gagne, R. J. &amp; Jaschhof, M. (2017) A Catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the World. 4 th Edition. Digital. U. S. Department of Agriculture, c / o Smithsonian Institution, Washington, D. C. Available from: https: // www. ars. usda. gov / ARSUser- Files / 80420580 / Gagne _ 2014 _ World _ Cecidomyiidae _ Catalog _ 3 rd _ Edition. pdf (accessed 23 December 2019)" type="book" year="2017">
<taxonomicName authority="Kolesik &amp; Gagné, 2020" authorityName="Kolesik &amp; Gagné" authorityYear="2020" box="[159,234,871,897]" genus="Gagne" pageId="61" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Gagné</taxonomicName>
&amp; Jaschhof 2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Elsayed, A. K. &amp; Yukawa, J. &amp; Tokuda, M." box="[441,671,871,897]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="123 - 160" refId="ref57745" refString="Elsayed, A. K., Yukawa, J. &amp; Tokuda, M. (2018 b) A taxonomic revision and molecular phylogeny of the eastern Palearctic species of the genera Schizomyia Kieffer and Asteralobia Kovalev (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae, Asphondyliini), with descriptions of five new species of Schizomyia from Japan. Zookeys, 808, 123 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 808.29679" type="journal article" year="2018">
Elsayed 
<emphasis box="[536,592,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
2018b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Elsayed, A. K. &amp; Yukawa, J. &amp; Tokuda, M." box="[681,909,871,897]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="348 - 360" refId="ref57823" refString="Elsayed, A. K., Yukawa, J. &amp; Tokuda, M. (2019 a) Two new species of Schizomyia (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) from Japan, with an updated key to larval, pupal and adult Schizomyia in Japan. Zookeys, 4688 (3), 348 - 360. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4688.3.2" type="journal article" year="2019">
Elsayed 
<emphasis box="[776,831,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
2019a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Elsayed, A. K. &amp; Wheeler, G. S. &amp; Purcell, M. &amp; Dyer, K. &amp; Zhan, J. &amp; Tokuda, M." box="[919,1149,871,897]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="429 - 436" refId="ref57893" refString="Elsayed, A. K., Wheeler, G. S., Purcell, M., Dyer, K., Zhan, J. &amp; Tokuda, M. (2019 b) A new Schizomyia species (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) inducing flower bud galls on Chinese tallow tree Triadica sebifera in its native range. Applied Entomology and Zoology, 54, 429 - 436. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13355 - 019 - 00639 - 9" type="journal article" year="2019">
Elsayed 
<emphasis box="[1014,1070,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
2019b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="da Silva dos Santos, D. S. &amp; Maia, V. C. &amp; Calado, D." pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="356 - 62" refId="ref61131" refString="da Silva dos Santos, D. S., Maia, V. C. &amp; Calado, D. (2019) Insect galls on Bauhinia cupulata (Fabaceae): morphotypes characterization and description of a new species of Schizomyia (Cecidomyiidae, Diptera). Revista Brasiliera de Entomologia, 63 (4), 356 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. rbe. 2019.07.002" type="journal article" year="2019">
da Silva dos Santos 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). The three show remarkable diversity and their generic placement will need to be evaluated when the genus as a whole undergoes restudy. Several structures of some of these three species are odd for the genus: female cerci of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,286,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laporteae">
<emphasis box="[151,286,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">S. laporteae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are no longer distinct but incorporated into the needle-like protrusible part of ovipositor; male cerci of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,333,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villebrunneae">
<emphasis box="[151,333,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">S. villebrunneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are incised caudally instead of being evenly convex; and gonostylar teeth are solid in 
<taxonomicName box="[1294,1429,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laporteae">
<emphasis box="[1294,1429,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">S. laporteae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, missing in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dandy" authorityYear="1931" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" box="[274,383,1051,1077]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ottochloa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis box="[274,383,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">S. nodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and spiny and narrow in 
<taxonomicName box="[675,857,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villebrunneae">
<emphasis box="[675,857,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">S. villebrunneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
